<li>13 were from Sydney: 4 south western-, 5 western-, 2 inner west-, and 1 south eastern-
<ul><li>3 were from Nepean Blue Mountains</li></ul></li></ul>
<p>The total number of COVID related deaths in NSW was now 408 since the beginning of the pandemic, 352 during the NSW Delta outbreak.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup><br />National deaths rose to 1,307.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>
</p><p>Also on on 30 September by 11:59pm, at least 65% of the over-16 population in NSW were fully vaccinated. Over 87% had received one dose.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h5><span class="mw-headline" id="Regional_lockdown_changes">Regional lockdown changes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_in_New_South_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Regional lockdown changes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h5>
<p>On 30 September there were multiple changes, including extensions and additions, to stay-at-home orders in NSW regional areas: 
</p>
<ul><li>Stay-at-home orders were put in place for 7 days from 3pm in Snowy Monaro LGA. The orders apply to anyone who was in the LGA since 22 September<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21_271-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21-271">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<ul><li>Stay-at-home orders were put in place until 11 October from 12 midnight in the Kyogle and Narromine LGAs. The orders apply to anyone who was in:<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-kyo-narr-lckdwn-30sept&#39;21_272-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-kyo-narr-lckdwn-30sept&#39;21-272">&#91;270&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li>Kyogle since 21 September</li>
<li>Narromine since 28 September</li></ul></li></ul>
<ul><li>Stay-at-home orders were extended by 7 days in 18 LGA regions, "due to the ongoing COVID-19 public health risk." The areas' lockdowns were due to ease on 4&#160;October, now they will extend to 11&#160;October. The regional LGAs affected are:<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21_271-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21-271">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li>Bathurst Regional, Bourke, City of Broken Hill, Central Coast, City of Cessnock, Dubbo Regional, Eurobodalla, Goulburn Mulwaree, Kiama, City of Lake Macquarie, City of Lithgow, City of Maitland, City of Newcastle, Port Stephens, Queanbeyan-Palerang Regional, City of Shellharbour, City of Shoalhaven, and Wingecarribee</li></ul></li></ul>
<ul><li>Mid-Western Regional, Hilltops and Walgett LGAs<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21_271-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21-271">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li>Stay-at-home orders lifted on 1 October</li></ul></li></ul>
<ul><li>In <a href="/wiki/Central_Darling_Shire_Council" class="mw-redirect" title="Central Darling Shire Council">Central Darling Shire Council</a>, stay-at-home orders will mostly be lifted on 1 October<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21_271-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21-271">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li>The exceptions are two towns:
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Menindee" class="mw-redirect" title="Menindee">Menindee</a> extended for 7 days</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wilcannia" title="Wilcannia">Wilcannia</a> extended until 11 October<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21_271-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-many-extend-30sept&#39;21-271">&#91;269&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>
<p>By 30 September new locally acquired cases of COVID-19 were up at 941.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21_268-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21-268">&#91;266&#93;</a></sup> Total new cases reported during the state's Delta outbreak rose to 56,500. The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 62,164. 1&#160;new case was acquired overseas, 1 from interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21_268-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21-268">&#91;266&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of the new cases: 231 (-10) were from South Western Sydney LHD, 93 (+13) South East Sydney LHD, 177 (-10) Western Sydney LHD, 63  (-17)&#160;Sydney LHD, 42 (+4) Northern Sydney LHD, 45 (+11) Nepean Blue Mountains LHD, 82 (+27) Hunter New England LHD, 43 (19)&#160;Western LHD, 5&#160;Far West LHD, 82 (-12) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 36 (+13) Central Coast LHD, 26 (+8) Southern LHD and 3&#160;Northern NSW LHD. None were in "correctional settings". 12 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21_268-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21-268">&#91;266&#93;</a></sup> <br />• There were 1,090 COVID-19 cases in hospital, 213 in intensive care, 105&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were 120,993 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 17,126,433 tests. <br />• There were 26,504 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,544,341 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 6,444,398 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 9,988,739 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21_268-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-30sept&#39;21-268">&#91;266&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="October">October</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_in_New_South_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: October">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>On  1 October deaths of confirmed COVID cases were at 10 in the 24 hours to 8pm. This was down on 15 the day before, <sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> which equalled the state's highest 24-hour COVID-19 death toll on 28 September.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-29sept&#39;21_8-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-29sept&#39;21-8">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> 4 were not vaccinated, 5&#160;partially vaccinated, 1 had received 2 doses of COVID-19 vaccine. The deaths included:<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> 
</p>
<ul><li>6 men and 4 women</li>
<li>1 person in their 50s, 3 their 60s, 2 their 70s, 3 their 80s, 1 in their 90s</li>
<li>2 at home:
<ul><li>a man in his 60s (inner Sydney) <br /> – not vaccinated <br /> – diagnosed with COVID-19 following his death</li>
<li>a man in his 80s (Lake Macquarie region) <br /> – had one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine <br /> – underlying health conditions <br /> – under community care by the LHD</li></ul></li>
<li>a man in his 60s (western Sydney) <br /> – had two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine <br /> – underlying health conditions <br /> – acquired his infection at Mount Druitt Hospital</li>
<li>8 were from Sydney: 5 south western-, 2 western-, 1 inner city- Sydney
<ul><li>1 from Wollongong, 1 Lake Macquarie region</li></ul></li></ul>
<p>The total number of COVID related deaths in NSW was now 418 since the beginning of the pandemic, 362 during the NSW Delta outbreak.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup><br />National deaths rose to 1,321, including 5 deaths interstate.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (October 2021)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>
</p>
<dl><dt>Casino lockdown</dt></dl>
<p>Also on 1 October, the town of <a href="/wiki/Casino,_New_South_Wales" title="Casino, New South Wales">Casino</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Northern_Rivers" title="Northern Rivers">Northern Rivers</a> region went into lockdown at midnight until 11 October. The stay-at-home orders apply to residents, or visitors to Casino since 24 September.<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-casino-lckdwn-1oct&#39;21_273-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-casino-lckdwn-1oct&#39;21-273">&#91;271&#93;</a></sup> 
</p><p>By  1 October new locally acquired cases of COVID-19 were down to 864.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup> Total new cases reported during the state's Delta outbreak rose to 57,357. The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 63,023. 1&#160;new case was acquired overseas, 1 from interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of  the  new  cases: 188 (-43)  were from  South  Western  Sydney  LHD, 83 (-10) South East Sydney LHD, 167 (-10) Western Sydney LHD, 45 (-18)&#160;Sydney LHD, 35 (-7) Northern Sydney LHD, 44  Nepean  Blue Mountains LHD,  69 (-13) Hunter New England LHD,  48 (+5)&#160;Western LHD, 7&#160;Far West LHD, 96 (+14) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 36 Central Coast LHD, 20 (-6) Southern LHD and 3&#160;Northern NSW LHD. 4 were in "correctional settings". 7 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup> <br />• There were 1,055 COVID-19 cases in hospital, 210 in intensive care, 104&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were 112,334 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 17,238,767 tests. <br />• There were 26,530 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,570,871 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 6,531,099 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 10,101,970 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21_270-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-1oct&#39;21-270">&#91;268&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On  2 October deaths of confirmed COVID cases were at 10 in the 24 hours to 8pm.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> This was the same as the day before, but down on the 15 before that,<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> which equalled the state's highest 24-hour COVID-19 death toll on 28 September.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-29sept&#39;21_8-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-29sept&#39;21-8">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> 4 were not vaccinated, 4&#160;partially vaccinated, 2 had received 2 doses of COVID-19 vaccine. The deaths included:<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> 
</p>
<ul><li>4 men and 6 women</li>
<li>2 people in their 50s, 4 their 60s, 2 their 70s, 2 their 80s</li>
<li>2 at home:
<ul><li>a woman in her 50s (Eastern Suburbs) <br /> – had one dose of COVID-19 vaccine <br /> – diagnosed with COVID-19 after death</li>

<p>The total number of COVID related deaths in NSW was now 428 since the beginning of the pandemic, 372 during the NSW Delta outbreak.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup><br />National deaths rose to 1,334, including 3 deaths interstate.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>

The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 63,825. 1&#160;new case was acquired overseas, none from interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of  the  new  cases: 196 (+8)  were from  South  Western  Sydney  LHD, 71 (-12) South East Sydney LHD, 155 (-12) Western Sydney LHD, 73 (+28)&#160;Sydney LHD, 29 (-6)  Northern  Sydney LHD, 42 Nepean Blue Mountains LHD, 65 (-4) Hunter New England LHD, 19&#160;(-29)&#160;Western LHD, 6&#160;Far West LHD, 72 (-24) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 30 (-6) Central Coast LHD, 27 (+7) Southern LHD and 8&#160;(+5) Northern NSW LHD. 6 were in "correctional settings". 8 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> <br />• There were 1,005 (-50) COVID-19 cases in hospital, 202 in intensive care, 99&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were 98,266 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 17,337,033 tests. <br />• There were 23,636 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,594,507 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 6,625,201 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 10,219,708 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21_16-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-2oct&#39;21-16">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>

<dl><dt>Lismore lockdown</dt></dl>
<p>On 3 October, the <a href="/wiki/City_of_Lismore" title="City of Lismore">City of Lismore</a> LGA in the Northern Rivers region went into lockdown, again, at midnight until 11 October. The stay-at-home orders apply to residents who were in, or visitors to, Lismore since 28 September.<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-lsmre-lckdwn-3oct&#39;21_276-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-lsmre-lckdwn-3oct&#39;21-276">&#91;274&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>By  3 October new locally acquired cases of COVID-19 were down 146 on the previous 24 hours to 667.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> Total new cases reported during the state's Delta outbreak rose to 58,811. The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 64,479. 1&#160;new case was acquired overseas, none from interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of the new cases: 154 (-42)  were from  South  Western  Sydney  LHD,  64 (-7) South East Sydney LHD, 109 (-46) Western Sydney LHD, 36 (-37)&#160;Sydney LHD, 36 (+7) Northern Sydney LHD, 15 (-27) Nepean Blue Mountains LHD, 82 (+17) Hunter New England LHD, 34&#160;(+15)&#160;Western LHD, 4&#160;Far West LHD, 49 (-23) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 43 (+13) Central Coast LHD, 27 Southern LHD and 6&#160;Northern NSW LHD. 9 were in "correctional settings". 9 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup> <br />• There were 981 (-24) COVID-19 cases in hospital, 195 in intensive care, 93&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were 88,210 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 17,425,243 tests. <br />• There were 21,972 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,616,479 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 6,719,201 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 10,335,680 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21_274-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-3oct&#39;21-274">&#91;272&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On  4 October deaths of confirmed COVID cases were at 7 in the 24 hours to 8pm.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21_277-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21-277">&#91;275&#93;</a></sup> This was 1 more than the day before, 3 less than the day before that.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21_275-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21-275">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup> 5 were not vaccinated, 2&#160;partially vaccinated. The deaths included:<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21_277-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21-277">&#91;275&#93;</a></sup> 
</p>
<ul><li>6 men and 1 woman</li>
<li>1 person in their 50s, 2 their 60s, 3 their 70s, 1 their 80s</li>
<li>5 were from Sydney: 5 south western-, 1 western
<ul><li>1 Dubbo</li></ul></li></ul>
<p>The total number of COVID related deaths in NSW was now 441 since the beginning of the pandemic, 385 during the NSW Delta outbreak.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21_277-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21-277">&#91;275&#93;</a></sup><br />National deaths rose to at least 1,357, including 6 deaths interstate.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>
</p><p>By  4 October new locally acquired cases of COVID-19 were 623, down by 44 on the previous day.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21_275-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21-275">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup> Total new cases reported during the state's Delta outbreak rose to 59,419. The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 65,090. No new case was acquired  overseas,  or  from  interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21_275-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21-275">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of the new cases:  144 (-10)  were from  South  Western  Sydney  LHD,  52 (-12) South East Sydney LHD, 103 (-6) Western Sydney LHD,  51 (+15)&#160;Sydney LHD, 18 (-18) Northern Sydney LHD, 25 (+10) Nepean Blue Mountains LHD, 59 (-23) Hunter New England LHD, 23&#160;(-11)&#160;Western LHD, 1 (-3)&#160;Far West LHD, 77 (+28) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 32 (-11) Central Coast LHD, 21 (-6) Southern LHD, 4&#160;Northern NSW LHD, 3 Mid North Coast LHD, and 1 Murrumbidgee LHD. 3 were in "correctional settings". 6 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21_275-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21-275">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup> <br /> • There were 959 (-22) COVID-19 cases in hospital, 193 in intensive care, 97&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were 88,210 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 17,425,243 tests. <br />• There were 13,045 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,629,524 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 6,763,470 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 10,392,994 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21_275-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-4oct&#39;21-275">&#91;273&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dt>Lockdown changes</dt></dl>
<p>On 4 October there were several lockdown changes in regional NSW:
</p>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Gunnedah_Shire" title="Gunnedah Shire">Gunnedah Shire</a> LGA in the <a href="/wiki/North_West_Slopes" title="North West Slopes">North West Slopes</a> region went into lockdown, again, at midnight until 11 October. The stay-at-home orders apply to residents who were in, or visitors to, Gunnedah since 27 September.<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-gundh-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21_278-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-gundh-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21-278">&#91;276&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<ul><li>in the <a href="/wiki/Mid_North_Coast" title="Mid North Coast">Mid North Coast</a> LGA postcodes 2430 (including <a href="/wiki/Taree" title="Taree">Taree</a>), and 2428 (including <a href="/wiki/Forster,_New_South_Wales" title="Forster, New South Wales">Forster</a> and <a href="/wiki/Tuncurry,_New_South_Wales" title="Tuncurry, New South Wales">Tuncurry</a>), went into lockdown at midnight until 11 October. The stay-at-home orders apply to residents who were in, or visitors to, those areas since 27 September.<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-midnthcst-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21_279-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-midnthcst-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21-279">&#91;277&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<ul><li>in <a href="/wiki/Muswellbrook_Shire" title="Muswellbrook Shire">Muswellbrook Shire</a> LGA in the <a href="/wiki/Hunter_Region" title="Hunter Region">Hunter Region</a> their lockdown was extended until 11 October.<sup id="cite_ref-nsw-health-midnthcst-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21_279-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nsw-health-midnthcst-lckdwn-4oct&#39;21-279">&#91;277&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>

This was up on 6 the day before, <sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21_277-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-5oct&#39;21-277">&#91;275&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-6oct&#39;21_280-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-6oct&#39;21-280">&#91;278&#93;</a></sup> 3 were not vaccinated, 4&#160;partially vaccinated, 3 had received 2 doses of COVID-19 vaccine. <h5><span class="mw-headline" id="State_lockdown_eased">State lockdown eased</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_in_New_South_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: State lockdown eased">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h5>
<p>On 11 October, which some news media dubbed "Freedom Day", the 107 day lockdown in NSW was eased, mostly for the fully vaccinated. Stay-at-home orders were removed for them; non-essential retailers, hairdressers, and hospitality venues were among those able to re-open to people who could prove their full-vaccinated status; masks were no longer mandatory in the open, though still required indoors in public places and on public transport.<sup id="cite_ref-abc-nsw-107-day-lckdn-eased-11oct&#39;21_287-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-abc-nsw-107-day-lckdn-eased-11oct&#39;21-287">&#91;285&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-abc-nsw-chngs-expl-11oct&#39;21_288-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-abc-nsw-chngs-expl-11oct&#39;21-288">&#91;286&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The same day, full COVID-19 vaccination reached 75.2%, and 90.8% had received one dose.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-13oct&#39;21_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-13oct&#39;21-18">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>By 11 October new locally acquired cases of COVID-19 were 496, up by 22 on the previous day.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21_285-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21-285">&#91;283&#93;</a></sup> Total new cases reported during the state's Delta outbreak were 63,338. The total number of confirmed cases in NSW reached 69,016. 2 new cases were acquired overseas, 0 from interstate.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21_285-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21-285">&#91;283&#93;</a></sup> <br />• Of the new cases: 113 (+7) were from South Western Sydney LHD, 42 (+2) South East Sydney LHD, 94 (+17) Western Sydney LHD, 36 (+4)&#160;Sydney LHD, 13 (-7) Northern Sydney LHD, 23 (+3) Nepean Blue Mountains LHD, 82 (+26) Hunter New England LHD, 13&#160;(-4)&#160;Western LHD, 4 (+3) Far West LHD, 38 (-20) Illawarra-Shoalhaven LHD, 21 (-5) Central Coast LHD, 6 (+5) Southern LHD, 4&#160;(-1)&#160;Northern NSW LHD, and 1 Murrumbidgee LHD. 1 was in "correctional settings". 0 were not yet assigned to any LHD.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21_285-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21-285">&#91;283&#93;</a></sup> <br />• There were 769 (-25) COVID-19 cases in hospital, 153 (-6) in intensive care, 71 (-5)&#160;requiring ventilation. <br />• COVID-19 tests were  83,498 to 8pm for that day bringing the state total to 18,143,578 tests. <br />• There were 19,706 COVID-19 vaccinations administered, for 3,774,740 doses total, by NSW Health, plus another 7,241,547 doses administered by the GP network and other providers, for a state total to this date of 11,016,287 vaccinations.<sup id="cite_ref-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21_285-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-health-nsw-stats-11oct&#39;21-285">&#91;283&#93;</a></sup>

<dl><dt>80% full vaccination reached</dt></dl>
<p>On 16 October NSW reached 80% full vaccination. Because of this, for those who are fully vaccinated, from 18 October mask wearing requirements, among others, and restrictions on numbers attending gatherings were eased, allowing more people to visit at home, gather outside, and at "controlled" (seated, fenced or ticketed) outdoor events. Travel between Greater Sydney and regional NSW was not yet permitted.<sup id="cite_ref-abc-nsw-80%-full-vaccd-16oct&#39;21_19-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-abc-nsw-80%-full-vaccd-16oct&#39;21-19">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>
